DBFS[databricks file system] -- is a file storage layer in Databricks that lets you easily store and access files inside Databricks.
    they are 2 types:
        1. DBFS root(dbfs:)-manage by databricks- good for small files, notebooks exports, temp files
        2. mount points(/mnt/) - linked to your cloud storage 

mount points -
        pros = short path and easy to use
        cons = uses service principal or key - not very secure and not recommended
so we need to use ABDF path
ABDF PATH-
        pros = use RBAC(Role-Based Access Control) + managed identity
            secure and better of unity catalog
            -- this is recommended

